eir other, often better-known, dramatic works contributing to a fuller estimation of their literary careers.This book is an invaluable resource for scholars and students of early modern literature, drama, history, civic culture, pageantry, urban studies, cultural geography, book history, as well as the interested general reader.Pageantry and power won the 2011 David Bevington Award for the Best New Book in Early Drama Studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aLondon Lord Mayor's Show.  aartificers.  acultural history.  aearly modern period.  alivery companies.  amayoral politics.  apageant writers.  apageantry.  apower.  aprinted pamphlets.1 aHill, Tracey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/9781526125101zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526125101zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526125101/original  a978-3-11-128363-0 Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA